    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Freshness and Completeness Checks for RAG Sources"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Two of the most operationally important data quality checks for a Claude RAG pipeline are freshness and completeness. Freshness ensures that the documents Claude retrieves reflect current reality, not a snapshot from months ago. Completeness ensures that every chunk carries the metadata fields required for ACL enforcement, lineage tracking, and data classification. Both checks must be automated, scheduled, and wired to remediation actions — not just reported."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Freshness and completeness check pipeline diagram",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The pipeline above shows the two checks in sequence: the freshness checker compares each source's last-modified timestamp against its declared refresh policy, then the completeness checker scans all chunks for required metadata fields. The action router routes each source to the correct outcome: serve, re-ingest, quarantine, or alert."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Freshness Checks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Freshness is a property of a source document, not an individual chunk. If the source document has changed since it was last ingested, all chunks derived from it are stale — even if each individual chunk still passes a metadata completeness check."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Freshness Policy Registry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datetime import timedelta\n\n# Maps source_id prefix patterns to their maximum permitted age.\n# Refresh policies are set by domain stewards and recorded in the asset register.\n\nFRESHNESS_POLICIES: dict[str, timedelta] = {\n    \"legal-policy\":          timedelta(days=90),\n    \"hr-handbook\":           timedelta(days=180),\n    \"product-pricing\":       timedelta(days=7),\n    \"compliance-runbooks\":   timedelta(days=30),\n    \"api-reference\":         timedelta(days=14),\n    \"support-faq\":           timedelta(days=14),\n    \"executive-comms\":       timedelta(days=365),\n    \"financial-reports\":     timedelta(days=90),\n}\n\ndef get_freshness_policy(source_id: str) -> timedelta | None:\n    for prefix, policy in FRESHNESS_POLICIES.items():\n        if source_id.startswith(prefix):\n            return policy\n    return None  # No policy declared — steward must set one before approval\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Checking Source Freshness Against the Live System"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For each source in the corpus, compare the ingest_timestamp stored in chunk metadata against the actual last-modified date of the source document. The implementation varies by source system; here are patterns for the most common ones."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datetime import datetime, timezone\nimport boto3, json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef get_s3_last_modified(bucket: str, key: str) -> datetime:\n    s3 = boto3.client(\"s3\")\n    head = s3.head_object(Bucket=bucket, Key=key)\n    return head[\"LastModified\"].replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\ndef get_sharepoint_last_modified(site_url: str, file_path: str, access_token: str) -> datetime:\n    import requests\n    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {access_token}\"}\n    api = f\"{site_url}/_api/web/GetFileByServerRelativeUrl('{file_path}')/TimeLastModified\"\n    resp = requests.get(api, headers=headers, timeout=10)\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    ts = resp.json()[\"d\"][\"TimeLastModified\"]\n    # SharePoint returns /Date(ms)/ format\n    ms = int(ts.strip(\"/Date()\").split(\"+\")[0])\n    return datetime.fromtimestamp(ms / 1000, tz=timezone.utc)\n\ndef check_source_freshness(\n    source_id: str,\n    ingest_timestamp: str,\n    source_last_modified: datetime,\n) -> dict:\n    policy = get_freshness_policy(source_id)\n    if policy is None:\n        return {\"source_id\": source_id, \"status\": \"NO_POLICY\", \"stale\": False}\n\n    ingest_dt = datetime.fromisoformat(ingest_timestamp.rstrip(\"Z\")).replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n    now = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n    age_since_ingest = now - ingest_dt\n    doc_changed_after_ingest = source_last_modified > ingest_dt\n\n    stale = age_since_ingest > policy or doc_changed_after_ingest\n    return {\n        \"source_id\": source_id,\n        \"ingest_timestamp\": ingest_timestamp,\n        \"source_last_modified\": source_last_modified.isoformat(),\n        \"age_days\": age_since_ingest.days,\n        \"policy_days\": policy.days,\n        \"doc_changed_after_ingest\": doc_changed_after_ingest,\n        \"status\": \"STALE\" if stale else \"CURRENT\",\n        \"stale\": stale,\n    }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated Re-Ingest Scheduling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\nREINGEST_QUEUE = Path(\"queues/reingest.jsonl\")\n\ndef schedule_reingest(source_id: str, reason: str, priority: str = \"normal\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Queue a source for re-ingestion. Consumed by the ingestion worker.\n    Priority: 'high' (run within 4h), 'normal' (run in next batch), 'low' (weekly batch).\n    \"\"\"\n    record = {\n        \"source_id\": source_id,\n        \"queued_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"reason\": reason,\n        \"priority\": priority,\n        \"status\": \"pending\",\n    }\n    with REINGEST_QUEUE.open(\"a\") as f:\n        f.write(json.dumps(record) + \"\\n\")\n    print(f\"Queued re-ingest for {source_id} (priority={priority}): {reason}\")\n\ndef run_freshness_sweep(collection):\n    \"\"\"Check all sources and queue stale ones for re-ingest.\"\"\"\n    results = collection.get(include=[\"metadatas\"])\n    seen: dict[str, str] = {}  # source_id → ingest_timestamp\n\n    for meta in results[\"metadatas\"]:\n        src = meta.get(\"source_id\", \"\")\n        ts = meta.get(\"ingest_timestamp\", \"\")\n        if src and (src not in seen or ts > seen[src]):\n            seen[src] = ts\n\n    for source_id, ingest_ts in seen.items():\n        # In a real pipeline, fetch last_modified from the source system here.\n        # For illustration, we assume a helper returns the real value:\n        # last_modified = fetch_source_last_modified(source_id)\n        # result = check_source_freshness(source_id, ingest_ts, last_modified)\n        policy = get_freshness_policy(source_id)\n        if not policy:\n            print(f\"WARNING: No freshness policy for {source_id}\")\n            continue\n        ingest_dt = __import__(\"datetime\").datetime.fromisoformat(\n            ingest_ts.rstrip(\"Z\")).replace(tzinfo=__import__(\"datetime\").timezone.utc)\n        age = __import__(\"datetime\").datetime.now(\n            __import__(\"datetime\").timezone.utc) - ingest_dt\n        if age > policy:\n            schedule_reingest(source_id, reason=f\"age {age.days}d > policy {policy.days}d\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
