            "type": "text",
            "text": "Completeness Checks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Completeness checks verify that every chunk in the vector store carries the fields the application relies on. Missing fields cause silent failures: a chunk without an ACL field is either inaccessible (safe but broken) or accessible to everyone (a potential data leak), depending on how the retrieval code handles the missing value."
          }
        ]
