            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Freshness checks compare each source document's last-modified timestamp against the ingest_timestamp stored in vector store metadata, applying a per-source refresh policy set by the domain steward. Stale sources are queued for re-ingest automatically. Completeness checks scan every chunk for the five required metadata fields — source_id, classification, ACL, ingest_timestamp, and content_hash — and quarantine any chunk missing a required field so it cannot be retrieved. Both checks run on schedule and immediately after every ingest via a post-ingest hook. Alert P1 when completeness drops below 95% or when a high-priority source becomes stale; P2 for less severe breaches. These two checks, automated and enforced, are the foundation of a trustworthy RAG corpus."
          }
        ]
      }
